\pard\f0\fs28 Dioecious or with hermaphrodite flowers; stems elongated. Leaves submerged, verticillate or sometimes opposite, sessile, usually linear, with 2 minute, entire nodal scales. Flowers pollinated at the water-surface. Spathes tubular, axillary, sessile, 1-flowered. Petals subequalling the sepals. Stamens usually 9. Ovary sessile within the spathe, attenuated into a long, filiform beak; styles 3, usually 2-lobed, free.
